": [{\"begin\": 569, \"end\": 576, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.092599588473887e-14, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Like at SW19, he has confirmed he will only compete in the doubles, where he will partner Dan Evans.\", \"from\": 771, \"to\": 871, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 861, \"end\": 870, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daniel_J._Evans\", \"score\": 0.9078031651324319, \"rank\": 0.10156038048555764, \"text\": \"Dan Evans\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daniel_J._Evans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daniel_J._Evans\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The four-time Olympic medallist, 30, made his Games debut in 2008 at the age of just 14 and has since become a stalwart of the Team GB diving line-up.\", \"from\": 873, \"to\": 1023, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"After claiming bronze in London and Rio, Daley finally ended his long wait for Olympic gold at Tokyo 2020 with victory in the 10-metre synchro event alongside Matty Lee.\", \"from\": 1025, \"to\": 1194, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1050, \"end\": 1056, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999990227638819, \"rank\": 9.706998532914237e-07, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}, {\"begin\": 1061, \"end\": 1064, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5684927138714808e-20, \"text\": \"Rio\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1184, \"end\": 1193, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matty_Lee\", \"s